2.43.0

Description: Fix CVE-2026-56368 memory leak in raw pixel coders
 ImageMagick6 leaks the QuantumInfo allocation when OpenBlob() fails on the
 output target inside the Write*Image() routines of the raw pixel coders
 (BGR, CMYK, GRAY, RGB, YCbCr). The early-return path after a failed
 OpenBlob() did not call DestroyQuantumInfo(), so a remote attacker that can
 cause repeated failed writes of crafted images could drive the process into
 memory exhaustion (CWE-401 / denial of service).
 .
 Backport of the upstream ImageMagick6 fix to 6.9.11.60 as shipped in
 Debian bookworm. The change is the same idempotent pattern repeated 19
 times across the 5 coder files: insert
 quantum_info=DestroyQuantumInfo(quantum_info); before return(status); on
 the OpenBlob-failure branch. DestroyQuantumInfo is already declared in
 magick/quantum.h on this branch, so no new symbols are introduced.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/eeab39181be971c1b5871dbb82a3d2a666454772
Author: Dirk Lemstra <dirk@lemstra.org>
Bug: https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/security/advisories/GHSA-wfx3-6g53-9fgc
Last-Update: 2026-06-27
